                        <head>95. Summary of Conclusions of a Washington Special Actions Group
                                Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d95fn1">Source: National
                                Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                                Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box
                                H–117, Washington Special Actions Group, <gloss target="#t_WSAG_1">WSAG</gloss> Minutes (Originals) 7–27–72 to 9–20–73. Top
                                Secret; Sensitive. The meeting took place in the White House
                                Situation Room. The minutes are attached.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" from="1972-11-08T14:08:00-05:00" to="1972-11-08T15:20:00-05:00">November 8, 1972, 2:08–3:20 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline></opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Vietnam Planning</item>
                        </list>
